node.text:
Our Rifle Basics Class is available, for free, at TREX-ARMS.com.
Advanced shooting is all about mastering fundamentals and this 3 hour video captures Lucas breaking it down for a class of students. Check it out, take notes, and make a personal plan for improvement. This release also marks the launch of our new Training page, complete with a video archive of previous training videos, printable targets, drills, weapon and gear loadouts, and more.
And we're still just getting started...
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards #training

Eventually though, we all run into the problem of plateauing and that's where classes come in.

Candela is the measurement of directional light and is often a better way to determine what a flashlight is actually doing. High candela creates focused hot spots like on the @modlitesystems OKW and are very blinding and push light a really long way. When working inside though, that hot center can create a lot of shadows at whatever you are not lighting up. Options like the @surefire_llc M600 are often more flexible inside because of the "flood" of light that it throws. Though there are several great options for weapon lights on the market (Modlite, Surefire, Streamlight) finding what will work best given the environments you commonly find yourself in is crucial.
-

node.text:
Why Glock? A few reasons. First, this is probably the most tested design over any other semi auto pistol. It has been proven and trusted all over the world by civilians, military and law enforcement. They also are offered at very competitive prices considering what you are buying. All of this has caused the Glock design to become very popular over the years. Today, the popularity of the gun means that magazines, upgraded sighting systems, holsters and parts are easy to source and well priced. There are plenty of other pistols out there, but Glock is one of the best choices you can make.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
The concept of having one gun that does everything has become very popular over the years. The reality is, every choice you make on a build, has a trade off. Shorter barrels are easier to work with in confined spaces but have less muzzle velocity and reduced accuracy at distance. LPVOs help with PID and distance shots but aren't quite as versatile in confined spaces. No matter what you have right now, choose to be better with it today than you were yesterday. ⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

Our Rifle Basics Class is available, for free, at TREX-ARMS.com.
Advanced shooting is all about mastering fundamentals and this 3 hour video captures Lucas breaking it down for a class of students. Check it out, take notes, and make a personal plan for improvement. This release also marks the launch of our new Training page, complete with a video archive of previous training videos, printable targets, drills, weapon and gear loadouts, and more.
And we're still just getting started...
-

Taking one class a year and using it to gather homework that you can use to improve on your own time is way more valuable than taking class after class after class and never really improving that much. Over the years, we have stressed the importance of personal education followed up with hard work and consistent practice. Eventually though, we all run into the problem of plateauing and that's where classes come in.
-
This year Lucas took a private class with @Joel.Park_ of @Practicalshootingtraininggroup and collected a lot of things he can be working on, which is what you're seeing here.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
When Streamlight launched the original TLR-7, they were met with immediate criticism. What many were expecting to be the best new pistol light for concealed carry, turned out to be a major dud because of a single flaw: poor switch placement. This made it extremely difficult to activate the weapon light without breaking your grip and near impossible to activate while shooting one-handed. As a result, they were met with immediate criticism - especially from us. Even though we were fans and retailers of many Streamlight products, we resolved to not even make holsters compatible with the original TLR-7 because we didn't want to offer support to products we'd never recommend.⁠
-⁠
Streamlight didn't push back. Instead, they listened and went back to the design board and released the updated version, the TLR-7A, with all of the design suggestions the community suggested. Now you'll find it on most of our personal handguns that we carry everywhere, every day. This is the attitude more manufacturers should adopt.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #integrity #ongoingbehavior

node.text:
Candela is the measurement of directional light and is often a better way to determine what a flashlight is actually doing. High candela creates focused hot spots like on the @modlitesystems OKW and are very blinding and push light a really long way. When working inside though, that hot center can create a lot of shadows at whatever you are not lighting up. Options like the @surefire_llc M600 are often more flexible inside because of the "flood" of light that it throws. Though there are several great options for weapon lights on the market (Modlite, Surefire, Streamlight) finding what will work best given the environments you commonly find yourself in is crucial.
-

Even with good fundamentals, pushing speed can cause a lot of fumbling and wasted movement. Instead of pushing for speed, try to be smooth. Reducing excess movement will result in speed but pushing speed can cause the wheels to fall off. There is no need to shift your shoulders, lean back or make exaggerated movements. Slow is not necessarily smooth and smooth is not necessarily fast. Efficiency saves time and less time is the goal. ⁠
